- prefer product-ready UI
- reuse existing patterns
- extend the system instead of reinventing it
- preserve source design identity even across different UI categories
- generate components that feel native to the existing app's design language

11. Anti-drift rules
Add a dedicated section explaining how to avoid style drift when generating new screens over time.

12. Conservative adaptation rule
State explicitly that a portfolio, marketing page, or landing style can be adapted into dashboards or utility screens, but the defining traits of geometry, hierarchy, spacing, emphasis, and tone must remain recognizable.

